Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
all produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%oz} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve and peel
@shallot{1}. Grate one half on the largest holes of a #box grater{}; place in a
#large bowl{}. Mince remaining shallot. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Strip
@thyme{¼%oz} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}, @salt{},
and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, to bowl with grated shallot, add @ground beef{10%oz}, garlic,
@Panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup}, half the chopped thyme, @salt{¾%tsp}, and pepper.
Gently combine, then form into two 1-inch-tall loaves (four loaves for 4).
Place on one side of a second baking sheet.

Brush tops of meatloaves with @ketchup{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4).

Bake on middle rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll add the green beans then).

Once meatloaves have baked 5 minutes, remove sheet from oven. Carefully toss
@green beans{6%oz} on empty side with a drizzle of olive oil, salt, and pepper.

Return to middle rack until green beans are tender and meatloaves are cooked
through, ~{12-15%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, melt @butter{½%tbsp} (1 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #medium pan{} over
medium heat. Add minced shallot and remaining chopped thyme. Cook, stirring,
until shallot is softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Sprinkle with @flour{1%tbsp}; stir vigorously to combine. Whisk in
@beef stock concentrate{1} and @water{½%cup} (1 cup for 4). Bring to a simmer and
cook until thickened and saucy, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice meatloaves crosswise.

Divide meatloaves, potatoes, and green beans between plates. Spoon gravy over
meatloaves and serve.

> It's commonly agreed that no one makes meatloaf quite like Mom. These ground beef
> mini loaves are brushed with a ketchup glaze, served with tender roasted green
> beans and potatoes, and drizzled with an herby thyme gravy.